item.label: Dura/Arachnoid
item.name: Dura_Arachnoid
item.description: The dura & arachnoid refers to a combination of the two outer layers of the meninges, i. e. dura mater and arachnoid mater.

item.label: Spinal cord
item.name: Spinal cord
item.description: The spinal cord is that portion of the central nervous system that extends from the medulla to the conus medullaris. It consists of 31 segments (8 cervical, 12 thoracic, 5 lumbar, 5 sacral, 1 coccygeal) and has enlargements at the levels serving the limbs (C5 - T1 and L2 - S3).

item.label: Cauda equina
item.name: Cauda equina
item.description: The cauda equina is a collection of lumbar and sacral spinal nerve roots (motor and sensory) located caudal to the last spinal cord segment and within the lumbar cistern as the nerve roots travel between the spinal cord and their respective intervertebral foramina.

item.label: Filum terminale
item.name: Filum terminale
item.description: The filum terminale is an extension of pia mater from the caudal end of the spinal cord that attaches to the end of the dural sac surrounding the spinal cord. It is located within the lumbar cistern along with the nerve roots of the cauda equina.
